. This jargon-free, insightful and long-term analysis of a dangerous crisis is an invaluable book for academics and students alike. It is also an effective tool for policy-makers, citizens and business people who require an accessible and in-depth appraisal of a continuing catastrophe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCurrency questionzEuropean Union countries. 0aMonetary policyzEuropean Union countries. 4aManchester Digital Textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Economic Policy.2bisacsh  aCoal and Steel Community.  aEU decision-making.  aEU financial emergency.  aFrance.  aGermany.  aMaastricht Treaty.  aborderless Europe.  ademocratic process.  aeurozone.  asingle currency.1 aGallagher, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615354840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526153548423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526153548/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles